text: The 1934 Austrian Athletics Championships () was the year's national championship in outdoor track and field for Austria. It consisted of 32 events: 23 events for men and 9 events for women. ==Results== ===Men=== 100 metres Berger (WAF) 11.2" 200 metres Gudenus (WAF) 22.6" 400 metres Radnitz (Vienna) 50.0" 800 metres Erdinger (Vienna) 1' 59.4 1500 metres Simacek (Cricketer) 4' 09.6" 5000 metres Leban (Heer) 15' 48.4" 10000 metres Leitgeb (Heer) 34' 11" 25000 metres Tuschek (WAC) 1h 24' 27" Marathon Tuschek (WAC) 2h 39' 47" 110 m hurdles Langmayr (Reichsbund) 15" 400 m hurdles Leitner (Leoben) 56.6" 3000 m steeplechase Simacek (Cricket) 10' 25" High jump Neuruhrer (Vienna) 1.75 m. Pole vault Huber (Cricketer) 3.60 m. Long jump Ing. Geisler (WAF) 6.70 m. Triple jump Schwertberger (WAF) 13.19 m. Shot put Coufahl (Vienna) 13.66 m. Shot put (2-handed) Vetter (WAC) 24.69 m. Discus throw Janauschek (Reichsbund) 44.67 m. Discus throw (2-handed) Janauschek (Reichsbund) 80.06 m. Hammer throw Janausch (Reichsbund) 43.97 m. Javelin throw Nawratil (Reichsbund) 59.25 m. Javelin throw (2-handed) Bezwoda (Cricket) 101.22 m. ===Women=== 100 metres Gerda Gottlieb (WAC) 12.9" 200 metres Johanna Vancura (WAC) 26.8" 800 metres Jiraschek (Danubia) 2' 33.4" 80 m hurdles Ditta Puchberger (WAF) 13.1" High jump Rosmini (weiss-rot-weiss) 1.45 m. Long jump Nowak (WAC) 5.06 m. Shot put Rosmini (weiss-rot-weiss) 10.97 m. Discus throw Lisl Perkaus (Danubia) 35.03 m.
